GENERAL FOODS CORPORATION, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. SEEMAN BROTHERS, Defendant-Appellee. No. 344. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 3, 1933. Melville Church and C. B. Des Jardins, both of Washington, D. C., and Geo. W. Case, of New York City, for appellant. Newton A. Burgess and Gifford, Scull & Burgess, all of New York City, for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and SWAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed on the opinion of Coxe, District Judge, below [66 F.(2d) 622] on the issue of noninfringement.
